## What to do
Move inject.go logic into `package inject` at `internal/inject/inject.go`.

### Exported API
```go
package inject

// HasFlag returns true if any of the given flag names appear in args.
// Checks --flag, -f, and --flag=value forms.
func HasFlag(args []string, flags ...string) bool

// GetLatestGitCommit runs `git log -1 --format=%s` to get the latest commit
// subject line. Returns "" on any error.
func GetLatestGitCommit() string

// GetSessionID checks CLAUDE_SESSION_ID env first, then OPENCODE_SESSION.
// Returns "" if neither is set.
func GetSessionID() string

// InjectFlags appends flags (actor, assignee, reason, session) to args based
// on the subcommand and logged-in handle. args[0] is the bd subcommand.
//
// Injection rules:
//   - --actor <handle>: ALL commands
//   - --assignee <handle>: create, update ONLY
//   - --reason <commit>: close ONLY (from latest git commit subject)
//   - --session <id>: close, update ONLY (from CLAUDE_SESSION_ID or OPENCODE_SESSION)
//
// If handle is empty, skip --assignee and --actor (return args unchanged).
func InjectFlags(args []string, handle string) []string
```

### Implementation
Copy the exact logic from root inject.go, renaming functions to be exported (capitalize first letter). No behavior changes. The package has zero internal dependencies — it only uses stdlib (`os`, `os/exec`, `strings`).

### Tests
Copy inject_test.go into internal/inject/inject_test.go. Change `package main` to `package inject`. Update all function calls: `hasFlag` → `HasFlag`, `getSessionID` → `GetSessionID`, `getLatestGitCommit` → `GetLatestGitCommit`, `injectFlags` → `InjectFlags`.

## Test
```
go test ./internal/inject/... -v -count=1
```
Must exit 0. All 3 test functions (TestHasFlag, TestGetSessionID, TestGetLatestGitCommit, TestInjectFlags) must pass.

